01:01.542 --> 01:02.668
Mom?

01:16.222 --> 01:18.349
Oh!

01:53.195 --> 01:55.195
Synced and corrected by Chitorafa
www.addic7ed.com

01:55.515 --> 01:56.722
What are you talking about?

01:56.805 --> 01:58.139
Scandal should totally
be your favorite show.

01:58.223 --> 02:00.851
The computer stuff is
completely unbelievable.

02:00.934 --> 02:03.353
But there's so much
torture. You love torture.

02:03.437 --> 02:07.816
What will your life be like in 15 years?

02:07.899 --> 02:10.693
That's what I want you to show
me in your first assignment.

02:10.776 --> 02:12.320
In groups of two, you're going to use

02:12.403 --> 02:14.114
the animation skills you've been learning

02:14.197 --> 02:17.325
to create a short video about what
you think your future looks like.

02:17.408 --> 02:19.244
Pair up!

02:19.327 --> 02:22.498
Wonder who Maya and Zig are working with.

02:22.581 --> 02:23.832
I think they have seizures

02:23.915 --> 02:25.626
if they're more than
five feet from each other.

02:28.253 --> 02:32.674
So, uh... did you maybe
wanna be my partner for this?

02:32.758 --> 02:34.257
Of course, dummy!

02:34.347 --> 02:36.058
I'll, uh, go grab a handout.

02:36.512 --> 02:38.346
That'll be fun.

02:40.431 --> 02:44.060
So, how's that whole "just being
friends" thing working out for you?

02:44.144 --> 02:45.353
Fine, why?

02:45.436 --> 02:47.898
"Oh, Grace, please be my partner.

02:47.981 --> 02:49.482
I simply can't live without you."

02:49.566 --> 02:51.527
Give it up. You love her.

02:51.610 --> 02:54.530
A little louder please. I don't
think the people in the back heard.

02:54.613 --> 02:56.573
Life's better out of the closet, Zo.

02:56.657 --> 02:59.660
- I don't even know if I'm gay.
- Right.

02:59.743 --> 03:01.578
I'm totally fine with just being friends.

03:01.662 --> 03:04.247
Besides, friendship is
basically dating, without...

03:04.330 --> 03:05.791
The good parts?

03:05.874 --> 03:07.834
You need to make your feelings known.

03:07.918 --> 03:09.545
And if she's not into girls, then sayonara.

03:10.503 --> 03:13.006
Look at her. That hair,

03:13.089 --> 03:15.466
those piercings...

03:15.551 --> 03:17.302
There is no way she's
doing that to attract boys.

03:17.385 --> 03:18.970
Shut up, please.

03:21.807 --> 03:25.686
Okay... I'll watch Scandal
if you watch Battlestar.

03:25.769 --> 03:27.688
Deal?

03:27.771 --> 03:29.898
Deal.

03:33.401 --> 03:34.402
Don't worry, I'll help you.

03:34.485 --> 03:36.446
- We'll just like, tutor, hang out.
- You sure?

03:36.530 --> 03:38.239
Yeah, it's like hanging out, except we...

03:38.323 --> 03:39.324
Oh...

03:41.451 --> 03:42.994
So, what do you think?

03:43.078 --> 03:47.207
Uh... it's so... different.

03:47.290 --> 03:49.543
- What's wrong with you?
- What do you mean what's wrong with me?

03:49.626 --> 03:51.878
Changing your hair is a cry
for help. Everyone knows that.

03:51.962 --> 03:54.840
And you've been different
since Winston broke up with you.

03:54.923 --> 03:57.843
- I just wanted a new look for this year.
- Are you sure?

03:57.926 --> 03:59.678
Because you've been really sad.

03:59.761 --> 04:00.804
I'm fine.

04:02.013 --> 04:04.683
Why don't we go out tonight?
Maybe you'll meet a cute boy.

04:05.559 --> 04:08.394
- I've got hats you can borrow.
- Thanks.

04:08.478 --> 04:10.271
I've already got other plans.

04:15.777 --> 04:17.821
So, how were they doing it?

04:17.904 --> 04:20.115
I already told you. I
couldn't see the dude's face.

04:20.197 --> 04:21.658
What does that even mean?

04:21.742 --> 04:23.952
- Were they like...
- No! Stop.

04:24.035 --> 04:26.747
I'm not gonna recount the
details of walking in on my mom...

04:26.830 --> 04:27.831
doing that.

04:27.914 --> 04:31.334
Hey, at least this means your mom's
not getting back together with your...

04:31.417 --> 04:33.128
lousy dad.

04:33.211 --> 04:34.545
You can say "abusive." He's earned it.

04:34.630 --> 04:35.797
Seriously.

04:35.881 --> 04:37.507
After everything he's put
our family through, like...

04:37.591 --> 04:38.925
I couldn't handle that.

04:39.009 --> 04:42.262
So, maybe there's a silver lining
to walking in on your mom getting...

04:42.345 --> 04:45.015
No! I think I have PTSD.

04:45.098 --> 04:46.432
I want to murder that
random my mom was with.

04:46.516 --> 04:47.601
Reasonable.

04:47.684 --> 04:49.185
I think that cutting the brakes on his car

04:49.269 --> 04:50.687
might really help me heal from this trauma.

04:50.771 --> 04:52.648
- That's what I'm talking about.
- Or maybe decapitation?

04:52.731 --> 04:55.025
I have some antique swords
kicking around the house.

04:55.108 --> 04:56.526
Well, there you go.

04:56.610 --> 04:58.695
I've also heard that bathing
in the blood of your enemies

04:58.779 --> 05:00.488
- is very therapeutic.
- Hmm.

05:03.909 --> 05:05.827
Your turn for institutionalized torture.

05:08.579 --> 05:10.206
So, are you gonna tell
your brother and sister?

05:10.290 --> 05:11.499
Nah, if my mom is having a fling,

05:11.582 --> 05:13.001
Frankie and Hunter don't need to know.

05:13.084 --> 05:15.754
I'm just gonna forget what
I saw. Or, you know... murder.

05:18.715 --> 05:20.801
What color do you think
your hair'll be in 15 years?

05:20.884 --> 05:24.095
- No clue.
- What about those piercings?

05:24.179 --> 05:26.807
Do you think they'll be all
stretched out and weird-looking?

05:36.733 --> 05:38.401
You okay?

05:40.153 --> 05:41.654
Whoa, what'd you do?

05:41.738 --> 05:44.365
I just made a dumb joke
about her piercings.

05:44.449 --> 05:46.910
- Uh-oh.
- What "uh-oh"?

05:46.993 --> 05:49.287
Well, you just don't want
to get on Grace's bad side.

05:49.370 --> 05:51.206
What are you talking
about? She's just a weirdo.

05:51.289 --> 05:53.124
I spilled soda near her laptop once

05:53.208 --> 05:55.210
and she didn't talk to
me for like, three weeks.

05:55.293 --> 05:59.672
Nah, Grace is always going
AWOL for no reason. Just chill.

06:02.425 --> 06:04.552
Okay, that is not chilling.

06:04.635 --> 06:07.388
I'm just texting her. Maybe
it wasn't about what I said.

06:15.063 --> 06:16.231
Who wants breast?

06:16.314 --> 06:17.733
It's very juicy.

06:17.816 --> 06:19.650
I'm gonna eat in my room.

06:19.735 --> 06:21.945
- Me, too.
- Sit down...

06:22.028 --> 06:23.363
both of you.

06:23.446 --> 06:25.365
We are going to have

06:25.448 --> 06:28.827
a nice meal together and we're
gonna talk about our days.

06:32.956 --> 06:34.457
So...

06:35.792 --> 06:37.293
what'd everyone do at school?

06:41.714 --> 06:43.133
I don't know why you're in such sour moods.

06:43.216 --> 06:46.011
I had a great day. I
tried a new Zumba class.

06:46.094 --> 06:47.595
- I feel very invigorated.
- Why don't we talk

06:47.678 --> 06:49.264
about Frankie's midlife-crisis hair?

06:49.347 --> 06:50.515
Why don't you shove it?

06:50.598 --> 06:52.851
Ugh, so much for a nice family dinner.

06:56.062 --> 06:58.148
Dude, what's your problem? Your
weirdo stat's been up today.

07:00.358 --> 07:02.360
Look, well, this morning, I... I kinda...

07:02.443 --> 07:04.320
That was the school. Uh...

07:04.404 --> 07:06.740
They want us to come and talk
to Principal Simpson tomorrow.

07:06.823 --> 07:09.659
- What'd you do now, idiot?
- For once, I have no idea.

07:09.743 --> 07:11.661
Apparently you threatened another student.

07:11.745 --> 07:12.871
What?

07:18.084 --> 07:19.419
I think I'm here.

07:19.502 --> 07:21.629
And for the record, this is a bad idea.

07:21.712 --> 07:23.048
I have to explain the hand touch

07:23.131 --> 07:25.133
wasn't a big deal before she
blows it out of proportion.

07:25.216 --> 07:27.844
Yeah, showing up at her house unannounced
will totally send that message.

07:27.928 --> 07:30.806
Thanks for the pep talk. Text you later.

07:42.400 --> 07:43.860
Hi, can I help you?

07:43.944 --> 07:45.528
I'm ZoÃ«.

07:47.572 --> 07:49.365
A friend of Grace's.

07:49.449 --> 07:52.035
Oh, um... Grace isn't home.

07:52.118 --> 07:55.163
- Do you know when she'll be back?
- Sorry.

08:23.636 --> 08:26.626
_

08:37.296 --> 08:41.275
_

08:41.876 --> 08:43.919
You're the only one who thinks so.

